meanings.definition: To surpass in performance or achievement.
meanings.sent1: She outdid her previous score in the math test.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outdid all his competitors in the race.
meanings.sent3: The student outdid himself by completing the project ahead of time.
meanings.sent4: Her dedication outdid everyone else's efforts in the competition.
meanings.sent5: The team's hard work outdid all expectations and won the championship.

meanings.sent1: He outdid his own record in the swimming competition.
meanings.sent2: The new model outdid the previous one in sales.
meanings.sent3: The chef outdid himself with the delicious dessert.
meanings.sent4: Her creativity outdid all other submissions in the art contest.
meanings.sent5: The singer's performance outdid all others and received a standing ovation.
